org.threadly.load

Interface StepResult


  • public interface StepResult

    Interface which represents the result of an executed test step. This provides if the test completed in error (via getError() being not null). As well as the runtime it took to execute the test step.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Check how long the test executed for until it completed normally, or in an error state.
      boolean wasMaintanceStep()
      Indicates if the result of this step was of type ScriptStepType.Maintenance or ScriptStepType.AsyncMaintenance.

    • Method Detail

      • wasMaintanceStep

        boolean wasMaintanceStep()
        Indicates if the result of this step was of type ScriptStepType.Maintenance or ScriptStepType.AsyncMaintenance. In either of those conditions the run time will always be zero, and thus should not be included in the resulting statistics.
        Returns:
        true if the step was a maintance step

      • getDescription

        java.lang.String getDescription()
        Get description of the test.
        Returns:

      • getRunTime

        long getRunTime(java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit desiredUnit)
        Check how long the test executed for until it completed normally, or in an error state.
        Parameters:
        desiredUnit - TimeUnit which result should be provided in
        Returns:
        nanosecond test executed for

      • getError

        java.lang.Throwable getError()
        Get the error result if it occurred. This will return null if the test completed normally.
        Returns:
        Thrown error during execution or null if executed normally
